external_knowledge:
- "stormy roads" metaphorically refers to highways with severe incidents;
- "turbulent regions" metaphorically refers to counties with severe incidents;
- "darkly marked" symbolizes the high-risk attributes (critical incidents, severe weather incidents, bad road conditions, bad light conditions) that exceed five occurrences;
- "harbingers of danger" implies places identified as high-risk due to the frequency of these severe incidents.

- 'storm rages' metaphorically represents the incidents;
- 'particular realm' refers to a specific county, in this case, the one with county_id = 1;
- 'specific breed of traveler' corresponds to a specific user type of highway user, represented by user_type_id = 1;
- 'certain thoroughfare' refers to a specific highway, represented by highway_id = 1;
- 'identities of the tempests' refers to the unique identifiers (IDs) of the incidents;
- 'names of the lands' refers to the names of the counties;
- 'kinds of voyagers' represents the types of highway users;
- 'titles of the paths' refers to the names of the highways;
- 'fury's intensity' is the severity of the incidents;
- 'toll in souls and bodies' represents the number of non-suicide fatalities and injuries.

sql:
SELECT i.severity, h.highway_name
FROM incidents AS i
INNER JOIN highways AS h ON i.highway_id = h.highway_id;

external_knowledge:
- "recent" refers to incidents occurring after 2020;
- "speedy travel" indicates user speed above 60 units;
- "casualties" implies the presence of non-suicide fatalities;
- "parties involved" includes the type of highway user and rail equipment.
